- Uses "Ãˆ" at the beginning.
- Uses "le" for most hours except 1:00, which uses "l'" (e.g., "Ãˆ l'una" instead of "Ãˆ le uno").
- Uses "ore" after the hour unless it is noon (mezzogiorno) or midnight (mezzanotte).
- Special cases:
